				\begin{document}$0.08~\mbox{m}^{2}$\end{document}—the surface area of one side panel). There are a fair number of rideshare launch opportunities into such an orbit, lowering the cost of the mission [25]. Limiting the distance at closest approach of the OGS at which the satellite passes to 750 km (i.e., the ground track passes within 500 km of the OGS), between 1 and 2 encounters per night can be expected, each with a total duration >440s\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
